and locked up like a schoolmarm.

223
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:48,000
But sometimes,
when we were alone...

224
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:56,200
Hair, hundreds of light-years long.

225
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:32,600
In the cosmic scheme of things,
I know little boys are small.

226
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,600
But some days they can be...

227
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:39,700
Some days, little boys can be...
giants.

228
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:46,400
That's beautiful... poetry.

229
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:54,600
This is Fran Ambrose,
on KTK, "Talk of the Town."

230
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:59,900
Tonight we're talking with a caller
who says he killed his mother.

231
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:01,700
